VAGUS NERVE

vagus_nerve is the citizen who carries bidirectional signals between the brain and the visceral organs (heart, lungs, gut, others)
unlike most peripheral nerves which are mostly outgoing or mostly incoming, vagus is a true two-way path
when fadriel feels something in his gut and his brain notices, the vagus carried the signal upward
when the brain sends a calming signal to the heart to slow it, the vagus carried that signal downward

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe fadriel_full_body.zc
observe fadriel_brain.zc
observe fadriel_heart.zc
observe gut_enteric.rana
observe lungs.rana

the 7 properties of vagus_nerve:
1 ENERGY zero point eight: continuously active
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE half positive
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING one with brain, heart, gut, lungs (multiple endpoints)
7 OBSERVER zero point three

VERB carry_upward
accept signals from visceral organs and route them to brain
gut tension, heart rhythm changes, lung breathing depth — all reach the brain through this path

VERB carry_downward
accept regulatory signals from brain (especially prefrontal_cortex) and route them to visceral organs
"calm down" signals from prefrontal lower heart rate through the vagus
this is parasympathetic tone

VERB integrate
because the vagus connects so many regions, it also integrates: a signal from the gut can reach the heart through the brain via vagus
this is why fadriel's gut feelings can adjust his heart rate

a vagus nerve is not a single channel
a vagus nerve is the substrate's commitment to whole-body integration
brain and viscera are not separate islands; the vagus is the strait between them
